## Connections for ESP32 + DHT11 + LED

### Components

* ESP32 Dev Board
* DHT11 Sensor
* LED
* 220Ω resistor (recommended)

---

## DHT11 Connections

| DHT11 Pin | Connect To ESP32 |
| --------- | ---------------- |
| VCC       | 3.3V             |
| GND       | GND              |
| DATA      | GPIO 4           |

### Note

* If using a bare DHT11 sensor, add a **10kΩ pull-up resistor** between DATA and VCC.
* If using a DHT11 module board, the resistor is usually already included.

---

## LED Connections

| LED Pin                 | Connect To                   |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Anode (+ longer leg)    | GPIO 2 through 220Ω resistor |
| Cathode (- shorter leg) | GND                          |

---

## Working

* The DHT11 Sensor reads temperature data.
* Motion values are simulated using `random()`.
* Battery level decreases when motion is high.
* LED blinks when battery drops below 20%.

---

## Pin Summary

* **GPIO 4** → DHT11 DATA
* **GPIO 2** → LED
* **3.3V** → DHT11 VCC
* **GND** → DHT11 GND + LED negative leg

****CODE:****

#include <DHT.h>

#define DHTPIN 4
#define DHTTYPE DHT11   // 🔹 Changed to DHT11
#define ledPin 2

DHT dht(DHTPIN, DHTTYPE);

int batteryLevel = 100;

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  pinMode(ledPin, OUTPUT);
  dht.begin();
}

void loop() {

  int motion = random(200, 2000);  // keep motion simulated if no MPU6050

  // 🔹 REAL temperature from DHT11
  float temperature = dht.readTemperature();

  if (isnan(temperature)) {
    Serial.println("Failed to read from DHT11!");
    delay(1000);
    return;
  }

  // 🔹 Battery drain logic
  if (motion > 1200 && batteryLevel > 0) {
    batteryLevel -= 10;
  }

  if (batteryLevel < 0)
    batteryLevel = 0;

  // 🔹 LED blink when battery low
  if (batteryLevel <= 20) {
    digitalWrite(ledPin, HIGH);
    delay(200);
    digitalWrite(ledPin, LOW);
    delay(200);
  } else {
    digitalWrite(ledPin, LOW);
  }

  Serial.print("Motion: ");
  Serial.print(motion);

  Serial.print(" | Temp: ");
  Serial.print(temperature);
  Serial.print(" °C");

  Serial.print(" | Battery: ");
  Serial.print(batteryLevel);
  Serial.println(" %");

  delay(1000);   // DHT11 needs ~1 second delay
}
